# Implementation Plan: Skin-Care & Beauty E-Commerce Platform (Revised)

This document outlines the detailed engineering plan to build a production-ready, full-stack skin-care and beauty products e-commerce platform using Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, MongoDB, Mongoose, NextAuth (session-based, no custom JWT), and Cloudinary.

---

## Technical Stack & Packages
We will install the following packages:
- `mongoose`: For structured schemas, relationships, validation, and indexing.
- `mongodb`: The underlying client for the NextAuth MongoDB adapter.
- `@auth/mongodb-adapter`: Official adapter for NextAuth to store users, accounts, and sessions in MongoDB.
- `next-auth`: Auth.js (v4/v5 compatibility) configured for database-backed session storage.
- `bcryptjs` & `@types/bcryptjs`: Hashing user passwords securely.
- `zod`: Type-safe schema validations for API endpoints, server actions, and forms.
- `cloudinary`: SDK for server-side product image upload and deletion.
- `lucide-react`: Clean icons.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Authentication Strategy**: NextAuth will be configured with `strategy: "database"`. This ensures a session document is created in MongoDB (`sessions` collection) upon login, and a secure HTTP-only session cookie (random UUID, no JWT) is stored on the client.
>
> **Tailwind CSS v4 Configuration**: We will customize colors and design systems directly inside `app/globals.css` using the new `@theme` block, aligning with Tailwind CSS v4 specifications.
>
> **Analytics Visualizations**: Since recharts/other React charts sometimes experience dependency friction with React 19, we will build **premium, responsive SVG-based charts** directly inside React components to guarantee 100% compatibility and native performance.

