## Security & Authentication Enhancements (New Plan)

### 1. Mandatory Authentication for Cart & Wishlist Actions
- Ensure that if a guest user clicks **Add to Cart**, **Add to Wishlist**, or **Buy Now**, they are immediately redirected to the `/login` page with a `callbackUrl` pointing back to the product details page.
- We will implement this check at the page level inside the inline server action handlers (`handleAddToCart`, `handleToggleWishlist`) on the Home, Catalog, and Product Detail pages.

### 2. DDoS & Brute-Force Rate Limiting (DDoS Protection)
- Implement a lightweight, in-memory Token Bucket rate-limiting middleware directly inside [proxy.ts](file:///c:/Users/ah076/OneDrive/Desktop/skin_prod/proxy.ts):
  - **General API/Page requests**: Limit to 100 requests per minute per IP address.
  - **Sensitive Auth endpoints** (`/login`, `/signup`, `/api/auth/*`): Limit to 15 requests per minute per IP to mitigate brute-force and credential-stuffing attacks.
  - If a client exceeds the limit, the middleware will immediately intercept the request and return an HTTP `429 Too Many Requests` response.

### 3. NoSQL Injection Mitigation (SQL Injection Equivalent)
- Ensure all query parameter inputs parsed from `searchParams` on the storefront and admin catalog actions are explicitly sanitized/cast to string primitives using `String(...)` before being supplied to Mongoose.
- This prevents attackers from passing complex query operators (e.g. `{ $ne: null }` instead of a search string) to modify query criteria.

### 4. Mobile Responsiveness & UI Polishing
- Review the customer and admin header layouts to ensure user name and avatar are fully visible and reflow neatly on smaller portrait screens.
- Test responsive grids and touch-friendly target elements across device frames.

